# Day 119: Moving Beyond Console Logs

**Topics Covered:**
1. The problem with Log files in Microservices.
2. What is the ELK Stack? (Elasticsearch, Logstash, Kibana).
3. Structured Logging (JSON format).
4. Using **Logback** to generate JSON logs.

**Learning Summary:**
In a Monolith, I could just check `app.log`. But in Microservices, I have 5 different services running in 5 containers. Checking 5 different log files is impossible. Today I learned the concept of **Centralized Logging**. We send all logs to one place (Elasticsearch) and view them in a UI (Kibana).
To make this easier, logs should be in JSON format, not plain text.

**Logback Configuration (logback-spring.xml):**
```xml
<configuration>
    <appender name="CONSOLE" class="ch.qos.logback.core.ConsoleAppender">
        <encoder class="net.logstash.logback.encoder.LogstashEncoder" />
    </appender>
    <root level="INFO">
        <appender-ref ref="CONSOLE" />
    </root>
</configuration>
